bilingual.source: The Boeing Dreamliner is so light it uses less fuel.
bilingual.target: 波音梦想飞机非常轻，所以使用更少燃料。

bilingual.source: The new samovar could make hot water much easier and could be transported anywhere, not to mention that it required much less fuel.
bilingual.target: 新的茶炊可以更容易地烧热水，并且可以随处运输，更不用说它需要的燃料更少。

bilingual.source: Biomass fuel can reduce dependence on fossil fuels.
bilingual.target: 生物质燃料可以减少对化石燃料的依赖。
这辆车需要燃料才能运行。
煤气炉使用气体作为燃料。

bilingual.source: They added fuel at the gas station.
bilingual.target: 他们在加油站加了燃料。
这辆卡车使用柴油作为燃料。

bilingual.source: He used pellets to fuel the stove.
bilingual.target: 他用颗粒来给炉子加燃料。

bilingual.source: The airplane is running low on fuel.
bilingual.target: 这架飞机的燃料快用完了。

list.abstract: FUEL（英 [ˈfjuːəl]，美 [ˈfjuːəl]），英语单词，作名词为燃料；燃烧剂；饮料。作动词为用燃料为（工厂；机器）提供能量；使…更旺；维持。短语搭配有fuel cell（燃料电池）。例句有“The use of wood for fuel.（使用木材作为燃料。）” FUEL相关名词类近义词有catalyst、elding。过去式为 fuelled。
Fuel最早在宾夕法尼亚哈里斯堡，也就是乐队的家乡的酒吧中演出。1996年Fuel录制了Porcelain，一张自己出资制作的EP。专辑包括Shimmer的最初版本，这首歌在当地的摇滚电台点播率很高。这些引起了Epic唱片公司的注意，并一年后与Fuel签约。

yingyinNormal.en: What were you doing with rocket fuel in your apartment?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你公寓里放火箭燃料干嘛？

yingyinNormal.en: We're in, we're out. We lose a little fuel, but we save a whole lot of time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一进一出，尽管费点燃料，但节省了很多时间。

yingyinNormal.en: We no longer have the fuel to visit both prospects, so we have to choose.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们的燃料不够去所有的星球，所以我们必须抉择。

yingyinNormal.en: We believe the Russians deduced that the rod was a fissionable fuel assembly. Believed they had it mastered and harnessed it at Chernobyl.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们认为俄国人的推断出那只燃料棒是可裂变燃料装置，认为他们在切尔诺贝利对其监管及控制。

yingyinNormal.en: But to my dad, food is fuel. You get picky about what you put in the tank, your engine is gonna die. Now shut up and eat your garbage.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但是对我老爸来说... 食物就是燃料，如果油箱没有燃料，你就会像发动不了的引擎般死掉。现在闭嘴，吃你的垃圾吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Man, you wouldn't believe what they charge for fuel out here. I might actually lose money on this job.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不知道这里的燃料有多贵，这差事我搞不好会赔本。

yingyinNormal.en: So, why was it his lucky day? Well, it turns out I had a little rocket fuel in the apartment.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为什么说那天是他的幸运日？因为我公寓里恰好就有一点火箭燃料。

yingyinNormal.en: Soviets managed to land unmanned probes. Somehow they must have picked up that fuel rod.
yingyinNormal.zh: 苏联人成功向月球发射了无人探测器，他们一定是以某种方式得到了燃料棒。

yingyinNormal.en: The Hermes. Well, they, it can't enter Mars orbit. Otherwise, they will never have enough fuel to, make it home.
yingyinNormal.zh: 赫尔墨斯号不能进入火星的轨道，要不他们就没有足够的燃料回家了。

yingyinNormal.en: In a traditional steel mill, furnaces are powered by burning fuel and can take days to reach the right temperature.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在传统的钢铁公司熔炉，由动力燃料燃烧驱动，一天之内就能达到正温。

yingyinNormal.en: Two drones shot down today. Ten fuel cells stolen in just over a month. These scavs are getting bolder.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天有两架无人机被击落。一个月内十节燃料电池被偷。这些掠夺者胆子越来越大了。

yingyinNormal.en: Instead of taking the Endurance into orbit around Miller's planet which would conserve fuel, but we would lose a lot of time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们不能绕着Miller的星球轨道，那样虽然节省燃料，但会消耗大量的时间。

yingyinNormal.en: That's right. These lines are live, still energized. And we're flying right at them in a big hunk of metal filled with jet fuel.
yingyinNormal.zh: 的确，这线是火线,，依然是带电的，我们就在它上空飞行，在装着燃料的大铁块里飞行。

yingyinNormal.en: Remarkable. In just under a half hour, 200 metric tons of fuel will ignite in a controlled explosion right beneath Howard's keister.
yingyinNormal.zh: 太震撼了，在半小时后，霍华德屁股的正下方将有200公吨燃料被定时爆炸装置点燃。

yingyinNormal.en: TARS, factor an orbit of Gargantua. Conserve fuel, minimize thrusting, but make sure we stay in range of Miller's planet. You got it?
yingyinNormal.zh: TARS，找一条卡冈图亚的轨道，节省燃料，少用推进器，但要确保在Miller星球的范围内，明白吗？

yingyinNormal.en: For decades, nuclear and coal have been the traditional stable workhorses that power the grid, but we're increasingly turning to a fossil fuel that's seen as both safer and cleaner, natural gas.
yingyinNormal.zh: 近几十年,核能和煤炭已经成为传统的稳定能源，但我们逐渐开始使用化石燃料，这被认为是更安全更清洁的能源，天然气。

yingyinNormal.en: So, while this would stimulate business, it would also encourage over consumption, or hoarding commodities, like food and fuel, raising their prices and leading to consumer shortages and even more inflation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这虽然能刺激商业活动，但也会造成过度消费或大量囤货，例如食物和燃料，使得价格攀升，导致供不应求，通膨更加恶化。

yingyinNormal.en: So, while this would stimulate business, it would also encourage over consumption, or hoarding commodities, like food and fuel, raising their prices and leading to consumer shortages and even more inflation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这虽然能刺激商业活动，但也会造成过度消费或大量囤货，例如食物和燃料，使得价格攀升，导致供不应求，通膨更加恶化。

yingyinNormal.en: In 1931, Thomas Edison confided to his friend, Henry Ford, "we are like tenant farmers, chopping down the fence around our house for fuel, when we should be using nature's inexhaustible sources of energy, sun, wind, and tide."
yingyinNormal.zh: 1931年，托马斯·爱迪生悄悄告诉他的朋友亨利·福特"，我们就像土地租用人，当我们需要时，砍我们房子周边的篱笆做燃料，自然就是取之不尽用之不竭的能源，太阳，风和潮水"。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, well, it's really cool. You fly to Moscow, they take you out to Kazakhstan, and then you get into a Russian Soyuz rocket which shoots you into a low earth orbit. Or just sits there on the launch pad because the Kazakhi mafia sold the rocket fuel on the black market.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这个过程就酷了，你先飞到莫斯科 然后他们带你去哈萨克斯坦，然后你再登上一个俄罗斯联盟号火箭，直接冲上低空地球轨道，又或是你只能呆坐在火箭发射台上，因为哈萨克黑手党把火箭燃料都拿到黑市上去卖了。

examination_example.sentence: Fossil <highlight>fuels</highlight> still generate roughly 85 percent of the world's energy supply.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 化石燃料仍占全球能源供应的大约85%。

examination_example.sentence: President Trump has underlined fossil <highlight>fuels</highlight> — especially coal — as the path to economic growth.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 特朗普总统强调化石燃料——尤其是煤炭——是经济增长的途径。

examination_example.sentence: Here was abundant <highlight>fuel</highlight> and lumber.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这里有丰富的燃料和木材。

examination_example.sentence: You'd think this might <highlight>fuel</highlight> the efficiency mind-set.

examination_example.sentence: Customers can bring shoes of any brand into an Adidas store to be shredded and turned into alternative <highlight>fuels</highlight> for energy creation.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 消费者可以把任何品牌的废旧鞋子带到阿迪达斯商店，经过粉碎处理后转化为创造能源的可替代燃料。

examination_example.sentence: One multinational company offers discounts to customers who bring in old footwear to be used as <highlight>fuel</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一家跨国公司鼓励消费者把穿旧的鞋子送去回收用作燃料，并为消费者提供折扣。

examination_example.sentence: Germany has just stated that they plan to ban the sale of vehicles using gasoline and diesel as <highlight>fuel</highlight> by 2030.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 德国刚刚宣布，他们计划到2030年禁止销售以汽油和柴油为燃料的汽车。

examination_example.sentence: In the past 12 months, Nigeria has suffered from a shrinking economy, a sliding currency, and a prolonged <highlight>fuel</highlight> shortage.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在过去的12个月中，尼日利亚(Nigeria)饱受经济萎缩、货币贬值及长期燃料短缺的困扰。

examination_example.sentence: A few countries are benefiting enormously from the consumption of fossil <highlight>fuels</highlight>, while contributing disproportionately to the global burden of climate change.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些国家依靠消耗化石燃料给自己牟取暴利的时候，同时极大地加重了全球气候变化的负担。

examination_example.sentence: The world looks to expand modern energy access to the billion or so people without it, while also cutting back on <highlight>fuels</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 全世界都在寻求让大约10亿没有现代能源的人获得现代能源，同时减少燃料消耗。

examination_example.sentence: Maintaining safe speeds and being electric, self-driving cars would drastically reduce pollution levels and dependency on non-renewable <highlight>fuels</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 自动驾驶汽车在保持安全速度和电动化的前提下，将大幅降低污染水平和对不可再生燃料的依赖。

examination_example.sentence: Green buildings like this aren't necessarily cost-efficient for the investor, but it does produce much less pollution than that caused by energy production through fossil <highlight>fuels</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对投资者来说，这样的环保建筑不一定具有成本效益，但它产生的污染远少于通过化石燃料产出能源所造成的污染。

examination_example.sentence: A quarter of this year's American grain harvest will be used to produce bio-<highlight>fuel</highlight> for cars.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 今年美国粮食收成的四分之一将用于生产汽车用的生物燃料。

word_level_phrase_info.brief_definition: 柴油燃料；柴油机燃料；柴油

examination_example.sentence: For example, people use fossil <highlight>fuels</highlight> (化石燃料) like coal and oil.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 例如，人们使用像煤和石油这样的化石燃料。

examination_example.sentence: For a <highlight>fuel</highlight> to be the best, people have to be able to afford it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们能够负担得起的燃料才是最好的燃料。

examination_example.sentence: At that time, petrol was expensive compared with other <highlight>fuels</highlight> (燃料).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在那个时代，与其他燃料相比，汽油很贵。
